		<p><b> Where do I access all Event related pages: </b></P>
		<p> On the header of the page, you'll find an option named "Events". If you hover your mouse over it you'll find all options for the Events. It has the options to see all Public Events, to search specific events, and to create an event</p>
		<p><b> What can I do in a Event Page?</b><p>
		<p>In the Event page you can do several things, including:<p>
			<ul>
			<li>Seeing all information for the event.</li>
			<li>Seeing and create posts and polls. Must be logged in to post</li>
			<li>Seeing all invited users</li>
			<li>Inviting users. Must be logged in to invite</li>
			</ul>
		<p><b> What is a public event? </b></p>
		<p> A public event is an event that everyone can see and participate in, logged in users or not. Private Events can only be seen by its creator and invited users.</p>
		<p><b> How to create an Event? </b></p>
		<p>Through the option on the page's header you can go to the Create Event page. On it you'll have inputs that are self explanatory. You can choose a name, location, date,description and photo for the event. You can also choose people to be invited before creating the event.</p>
		<p><b>How do I search for specific events?></b></p>
		<p>In the Search Event Page, which you can access through the Event option in the header. When you first enter the page all events you can access are there. You can click the advanced options to further filter your search. The options are:</p>
			<ul>
			<li>Type of Event</li>
			<li>Availabuility</li>
			<li>Search Order</li>
			</ul>
